 :tx/rationale "Create task: TAP-2: CLI stdin support for structured task documents — 'braid task create -' reads from stdin (INV-INTERFACE-008, ADR-INTERFACE-002). BACKGROUND: The positional title arg is the root cause of bloat — agents take the path of least friction (single string). The structured document format via stdin makes the correct approach equally frictionless: 'braid task create - <<EOF'. Format uses the SAME section markers that TASK-DECOMPOSE already parses: TITLE:, BACKGROUND:, ACCEPTANCE:, APPROACH:, FILE:, TRACES-TO:, PRIORITY:, TYPE:. When title is '-', read stdin and parse sections. Each section populates the corresponding :task/* datom. TITLE must be ≤120 chars (enforced). APPROACH: (1) In commands/mod.rs TaskAction::Create, when title == '-', read stdin. (2) Parse sections with simple line-prefix matching (same logic as TASK-DECOMPOSE). (3) Validate: TITLE required, ≤120 chars. (4) Pass parsed sections to create_task_datoms via new fields in CreateTaskParams. (5) Backward compat: when title != '-', existing single-string behavior unchanged. Tests: (A) 'echo TITLE: test | braid task create -' creates task with title 'test'. (B) Full structured document creates task with all sections populated. (C) Title > 120 chars is rejected with clear error. (D) Missing TITLE: section is rejected. (E) Backward compat: 'braid task create \"old style\"' still works. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/task.rs"
